thread.title: Gold Falls to 2018 Low on Stronger Dollar

author: Amrith Ramkumar
title: Gold Falls to 2018 Low on Stronger Dollar
text:
Gold prices fell to their lowest level of the year Thursday, hurt by a stronger dollar and concerns about higher interest rates.
Front-month gold for March delivery shed 1% to $1,302.90 a troy ounce on the Comex division of the New York Mercantile Exchange. Prices have fallen since hitting 17-month highs in late January with the dollar bouncing back from multiyear lows and worries about rates roiling markets.
